50|$|On 8 August 2013 a {{campaign}} group {{was set up}} to bring together the individuals and businesses affected by the <b>compulsory</b> <b>purchase</b> order that was in place for a number of years. The <b>compulsory</b> <b>purchase</b> has now officially expired. The aim of the campaign group was to seek compensation from Merseytram for the loss caused by the <b>compulsory</b> <b>purchase</b> order. A Freedom of Information request was also submitted to Merseytravel on 8 August 2013 with a view of obtaining the details of all land/building owners affected by the <b>compulsory</b> <b>purchase</b> order.|$|R
