50|$|<b>Compulsory</b> <b>purchase</b> only {{applies to}} the extent that it is {{necessary}} for the purchaser's purposes. Thus, for example, a water authority does not need to buy the freehold in land in order to run a sewer through it. An easement will normally suffice, so in such cases the water authority may only acquire an easement through the use of <b>compulsory</b> <b>purchase.</b>|$|R
